title: David Beckham jets home after night with Poppy Delevingne
text:
He spent the night before partying with model Poppy Delevingne.
And David Beckham seemed to be keeping a low-profile as he jetted out of Los Angeles airport on Thursday.
Possibly concealing the signs of a good night out, the 41-year-old former footballer donned a pair of dark shades as he strolled through the terminal.
Scroll down for video
Jet set style: He spent the night before partying with model Poppy Delevingne. And David Beckham seemed to be keeping a low-profile as he jetted out of LAX on Thursday
Opting for a neutral colour scheme, David teamed a black jumper with tracksuit bottoms.
Keeping comfy for the flight he also donned a pair of grey trainers and a khaki cap.
He finished off the look with a maroon rucksack and a chunky wristwatch.
Under cover: Possibly concealing the signs of a good night out, the 41-year-old former footballer donned a pair of dark shades as he strolled through the terminal
Having fun: David's flight came just hours after he was seen partying at West Hollywood bar The Friend with British model Poppy, 30
David's flight came just hours after he was seen partying at West Hollywood bar The Friend with British model Poppy, 30.
As pictures exclusively obtained by MailOnline show, the sportsman appeared to be a tad worse for wear, but remained the quintessential gentleman, holding a car door open for the beauty as they eventually made their exit.
Looking uncharacteristically unkempt in a crumpled khaki jacket with a red beanie, the Manchester United legend struggled to keep his eyes open as he left the bar.
Low-key: Keeping comfy for the flight David donned a pair of grey trainers and a khaki cap
He'll have plenty of time to sleep on the flight, however, as he'll no doubt be heading back to London to see wife Victoria and their four children.
David recently revealed that they had renewed their wedding vows in an intimate ceremony.
He said on Radio 4: 'We did throw a lot at it (the first wedding). We have renewed our vows since then and it was a lot more private, there was about six people there in our house.'
All about the accessories: David finished off the look with a maroon rucksack and a wristwatch
